Why Docker Exists?
==================
Because if we developed an application if we are giving this application access to our newly joined employee or QA team,he must and shd install same java versions,sql versions and all what exaclty we are using for that project otherwise may they will get errors,our application will not run,so  downloading manually application required tools from outside and mainting versions are so difficult.

What is docker?
===============
Docker is a tool that allows you to package your application and its entire environment into one unit.


Docker Architecture?
====================
Docker CLI--->to perform docker options like docker pull 
Docker Registry->to push our image or container to docekr registry so other can able to pull from here

Docker Commands 
===============
download image: docker pull <imagename>

Check Version : docker --version

Running Containers: docker ps

List containers which are present: docker ps -a 

Stop Container : docker stop <container Id>

Start Container :docker start <container Id>

Remove all stopped Containers: docker container prune

Create and run a new container from an image: docker run

Execute a command in a running container: docker exec


Build an image from a Dockerfile: docker build

Download an image from a registry: docker pull

Upload an image to a registry: docker push

List images: docker images

Authenticate to a registry: docker login

Log out from a registry: docker logout

Search Docker Hub for images: docker search

Show the Docker version information: docker version

Display system-wide information: docker info

To interactive docker images (ex for ubantu image): docker run -it ubantu

to exit from image: exit 


