Docker Volume
==============
Basically if we run image everytime it will create new container so ,we will loose our previous container data ,so if want mantain same data for all containers wee need to use volumes.



run image with volume
-----------------------------

docker run -d -v <name of the volume>:/app -e SERVER_PORT=9090 -p 8080:9090 <name of the imgae>:<version>

if we want create 2 containers stop first one and run again same above command.


See the volumes
---------------
docker volume ls

Remove Docker Volume
-------------------
docker volume rm <name of the volume>


Docker Compose
==============
Docker compose allows us to define and run multi-container docker applications using a yml file.
version:latest

services:
  app:
   image: docker-demo:1.0
   ports:
     - 9090:9090
   environment:
     - SERVER_PORT: 9090
   volumes: 
     - names-volume:/app

volumes: 
  names-volume

  to run this compose yml file we have to run below command
-------------------------------------------------------------

docker compose up

  to stop this compose yml file we have to run below command
-------------------------------------------------------------

docker compose down



